{"_id":"19S1vBdqvKy5ZeMv","name":"Truthsense","type":"invocation","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/png/saveknor.png","data":{"notes":"","description":"<table style=\"width: 98.8212%; height: 32px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Time to Perform:</strong> One minute</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Requirement:</strong> Silent prayer/concentration/gesture</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Allows the cleric to perceive when a person to whom s/he is speaking is telling a lie (i.e. something s/he does not actually believe). Only with Critical Success are lies of omission detected. The effect lasts for 5/15 minutes with MS/CS.</p>","source":"HMG PE Religion 10, Glossdex 39","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"diety":"Sávè-k'nôr","circle":2,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"ptPGLX4zqAaa1Zsn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-rituals-agrik.z80UPKcyoy7WrHnd"}}}
{"_id":"4y5xdonqMCZQoCs7","name":"Exorcism","type":"invocation","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/png/saveknor.png","data":{"notes":"","description":"<table style=\"width: 98.8212%; height: 32px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Time to Perform:</strong> Several hours</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Requirement:</strong> frequent touch/<em>mental conflict</em> (see <em>H&acirc;rnMaster GM Edition</em>) between the exorcist and the possessing spirit.</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>The removal of a possessing Aura (ethereal, demon, etc.,) from a victim. Greater demons may require CS to remove. The purpose of the invocation is to protect the exorcist from the ill-effects of mental conflict (at GM discretion). Even so, this is a highly variable, unpredictable and dangerous ritual.</p>","source":"HMG PE Religion 10, Glossdex 13","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"diety":"Sávè-k'nôr","circle":3,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"ptPGLX4zqAaa1Zsn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-rituals-agrik.z80UPKcyoy7WrHnd"}}}
{"_id":"EGMLjejlx0x5HbuG","name":"Summoning","type":"invocation","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/png/saveknor.png","data":{"notes":"","description":"<table style=\"width: 98.8212%; height: 32px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Time to Perform:</strong> About 5 minute</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Requirement:</strong> Prayer/gesture/cant/etc.</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Calls forth a denizen of the cleric&rsquo;s deity. A M&ocirc;rg&aacute;than might call the nearest g&ugrave;lm&ocirc;rvrin, an Agr&iacute;kan might call a V&rsquo;h&icirc;r, etc. The power and co-operation of the summoned creature may depend on the success level attained. It is difficult to predict how soon the summoned entity will appear or the nature or power of the entity that appears. See also COMMAND. The invocation has a limited range and will not summon creatures more than a league distant.</p>\n<p>However, if the invoker takes about an hour, draws a pentagram, burns copious amounts of incense, cants, etc., it may be possible to summon certain types of creatures from other <em>planes</em>. This type of summoning is limited to ethereal or demi-ethereal creatures, such as the V&rsquo;h&icirc;r, whose natural habitat is not of the world.</p>\n<p><strong>Optional Rules:</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp; (&nbsp; ) The ritual may be used to summon any ethereal demon/demigod whose true name is known.</p>\n<p>&nbsp; (&nbsp; ) With CS, an ethereal/demon/demigod whose true name is not known may be summoned.</p>","source":"HMG PE Religion 10, Glossdex 37","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"diety":"Sávè-k'nôr","circle":4,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"ptPGLX4zqAaa1Zsn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-rituals-agrik.z80UPKcyoy7WrHnd"}}}
{"name":"Curse","type":"invocation","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/png/agrik.png","data":{"notes":"","description":"<table style=\"width: 98.8212%; height: 32px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Time to Perform:</strong> Appr. one hour</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Requirement:</strong> Prayer/meditation/gesture/touch/verbal declaration</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>A curse is an attempt to call forth the displeasure of one&rsquo;s deity upon a victim. This is the opposite of a <em>blessing</em>. A successful curse manifests in any of several ways. A curse may be removed by an equivalent Blessing. Curses cannot kill or be randomly directed. The GM makes the success roll secretly (see Curse Table):</p>\n<p>Optional rules:</p>\n<p>&nbsp; ( ) GM may use Medical and/or Psyche tables in the <em>H&acirc;rnMaster GM Edition</em> to randomly generate curses.</p>\n<p>&nbsp; ( ) The curser may <em>attempt</em> to specify the nature of the curse, &ldquo;may your right index finger fester and drop off&rdquo;, by re-testing Ritual. If this option is allowed, failure on the 2<sup>nd</sup> roll causes the curse to fail or rebound.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width: 491px; height: 97px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10px; height: 16px;\"><strong>Success</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 103px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\"><strong>Effect</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10px; height: 16px;\"><strong>CF</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 103px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Invoker suffers a substantial curse.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10px; height: 16px;\"><strong>MF</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 103px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">No effect</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 33px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10px; height: 33px;\"><strong>MS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 103px; text-align: center; height: 33px;\">Victim sustains a 10% penalty on the next situation calling for luck (almost anything calling or a die roll).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10px; height: 16px;\"><strong>CS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 103px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">Victim suffers a <em>substantial </em>curse, such as an old wound/disfigurement or mental disorder</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","source":"HMG PE Religion 10, Glossdex 9","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"diety":"","circle":null,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"ptPGLX4zqAaa1Zsn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-rituals-agrik.z80UPKcyoy7WrHnd"}},"_id":"FymDhuypvGQ2149i"}
{"name":"Invisibility","type":"invocation","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/png/agrik.png","data":{"notes":"","description":"<table style=\"width: 98.8212%; height: 32px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Time to Perform:</strong> Appr. one minute</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Requirement:</strong> Prayer/gesture</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>This Invocation hides the invoker from observers; either <em>marginal</em> or <em>critical</em> invisibility may be achieved. This is not true invisibility since each potential observer tests half AWARENESS (or 2&times;Eyesight, whichever seems more appropriate in the situation) to detect the &ldquo;invisible&rdquo; invoker. If the observer&rsquo;s success level equals or exceeds the degree of &ldquo;invisibility&rdquo;, the observer sees the &ldquo;invisible&rdquo; invoker.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","source":"HMG PE Religion 10, Glossdex 20","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"diety":"","circle":null,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"ptPGLX4zqAaa1Zsn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-rituals-agrik.z80UPKcyoy7WrHnd"}},"_id":"GsuQkW3Fp7eQZZuV"}
{"_id":"GtA24nPB1ohRX6Tl","name":"Divination","type":"invocation","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/png/saveknor.png","data":{"notes":"","description":"<table style=\"width: 98.8212%; height: 32px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Time to Perform:</strong> 1-2 hours</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Requirement:</strong> Prayer/trance/meditation/conductive environment.</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Obtains information from the servants of the deity, from other planes of existence, or directly from the mind of the deity. The more specific the query, the greater the likelihood of success (yes/no questions are best). If the enquiry is more general, the EML is reduced.</p>\n<p>CS is needed to acquire <em>hidden</em> knowledge. CF may produce false or misleading information.</p>\n<p>Divination does not generate moral guidance or inform the invoker of the will of the deity (for which see COMMUNION).</p>","source":"HMG PE Religion 10, Glossdex 11","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"diety":"Sávè-k'nôr","circle":1,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"ptPGLX4zqAaa1Zsn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-rituals-agrik.z80UPKcyoy7WrHnd"}}}
{"_id":"IY10Vev4jXqvpd3U","name":"Communion","type":"invocation","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/png/saveknor.png","data":{"notes":"","description":"<table style=\"width: 98.8212%; height: 32px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Time to Perform:</strong> 1-60 minutes (depending on time available)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Requirement:</strong> Prayer/meditation</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>An attempt to commune with the spirit, and divine the <em>will</em> of the deity. Communion is used to seek moral &ldquo;guidance&rdquo; in various situations. Monks may use communion daily, others less often.</p>\n<p>If the deity has no particular moral or other requirement in the situation, it will not answer. If the deity does have a preference, it may or may not communicate it. Sometimes the deity wants its adherent to make her/his own decision.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","source":"HMG PE Religion 10, Glossdex 8","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"diety":"Sávè-k'nôr","circle":1,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"ptPGLX4zqAaa1Zsn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-rituals-agrik.z80UPKcyoy7WrHnd"}}}
{"_id":"IhAb86hyW2gk5tIy","name":"Protection","type":"invocation","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/png/saveknor.png","data":{"notes":"","description":"<table style=\"width: 98.8212%; height: 32px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Time to Perform:</strong> 30 seconds</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Requirement:</strong> Word and gesture (nothing special)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width: 491px; height: 80px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10px; height: 16px;\"><strong>Success</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 51px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\"><strong>Radius</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 25px; text-align: center;\"><strong>Duration</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 12px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\"><strong>Will Test</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 12px; text-align: center;\"><strong>Spirit</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10px; height: 16px;\"><strong>CS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 51px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">10 yards</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25px; text-align: center;\">3d6 hours</td>\n<td style=\"width: 12px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Will</td>\n<td style=\"width: 12px; text-align: center;\"><sup>1</sup>/<sub>4</sub> SPIRIT</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10px; height: 16px;\"><strong>MS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 51px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">5 yards</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25px; text-align: center;\">1d6 hours</td>\n<td style=\"width: 12px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">3x Will</td>\n<td style=\"width: 12px; text-align: center;\"><sup>1</sup>/<sub>2</sub> SPIRIT</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10px; height: 16px;\"><strong>MF/CF</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 51px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">n/a</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25px; text-align: center;\">n/a</td>\n<td style=\"width: 12px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">n/a</td>\n<td style=\"width: 12px; text-align: center;\">n/a</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Depending on the success level achieved, Protection creates a marginal or critical <em>zone of exclusion</em> which entities hostile to the Invoker are reluctant to enter. In order to enter the zone, the hostile entity must test <em>either</em>:</p>\n<p>&nbsp; (&nbsp; ) The multiple of WILL given on the <em>Protection</em> table. <strong>OR</strong><br />&nbsp; (&nbsp; ) The fraction of SPIRIT indicated on the <em>Protection</em> Table.</p>\n<p>The maximum zone radius is given (the invoker may specify any radius up to the maximum). Once established, the zone is not mobile; it is eliminated should the invoker leave it.</p>\n<p>The Duration given is <em>maximum</em>. The invoker may dissolve the zone at any time.</p>\n<p>Optional Rule:<br />&nbsp; (&nbsp; ) Bonus Effect ML 86+: The invoker has the option to keep the zone centred on her/his person. If this is done, the zone extends <em>radius</em> from the invoker wherever s/he goes.</p>","source":"HMG PE Religion 10, Glossdex 29","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"diety":"Sávè-k'nôr","circle":3,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"ptPGLX4zqAaa1Zsn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-rituals-agrik.z80UPKcyoy7WrHnd"}}}
{"_id":"N03X9DB5WueZkrgs","name":"Command","type":"invocation","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/png/saveknor.png","data":{"notes":"","description":"<table style=\"width: 98.8212%; height: 32px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Time to Perform:</strong> Appr. 5 seconds</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Requirement:</strong> Prayer/gesture</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>The ability to control the denizens of the deity, some/all of whom may be dangerous. Most deities have demi&ndash;divine or ethereal servants. Only such creatures are affected. A cleric can typically command only the denizens of its <em>own</em> deity.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width: 491px; height: 97px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 38px; height: 16px;\"><strong>CS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: left;\">Any servant of any deity may be banished. A denizen of one&rsquo;s own deity may be obliged to perform a minor task (GM discretion).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 38px; height: 16px;\"><strong>MS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: left;\">Hostile denizens of one&rsquo;s own religion may be banished, but creatures of other deities are not driven off (although they are probably made uncomfortable and, if not well&ndash;motivated to remain, may leave anyway).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 33px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 38px; height: 33px;\"><strong>MF</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; text-align: left; height: 33px;\">No effect (the target entity continues doing whatever it would have done anyway).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 38px; height: 16px;\"><strong>CF</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; text-align: left; height: 16px;\">The target entity becomes hostile (even if it was not already so).</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>DENIZENS:</strong> this term is used to describe the <em>special</em> creatures that &lsquo;belong&rsquo; to the deity; it is applied at GM discretion. Examples: the special creatures of Ilv&icirc;r include the &Igrave;vash&uacute;; those of Nav&eacute;h include the Gyt&eacute;vsha; those of Si&eacute;m include (some of) the Ils&icirc;ri, and so on.</p>","source":"HMG PE Religion 10, Glossdex 8","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"diety":"Sávè-k'nôr","circle":4,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"ptPGLX4zqAaa1Zsn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-rituals-agrik.z80UPKcyoy7WrHnd"}}}
{"_id":"SK4hR01Pm3Co6Bln","name":"Liturgy","type":"invocation","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/png/saveknor.png","data":{"notes":"","description":"<table style=\"width: 98.8212%; height: 32px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Time to Perform:</strong> 10-30 minutes</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Requirement:</strong> Communal prayer/meditation</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Liturgy is the spiritual joining-together of several priests/adherents for any of a number of purposes.</p>\n<p>The invocation is sometimes (rarely) used in religious services open to the public. If used to &ldquo;join&rdquo; several clerics, the group thus formed may jointly undertake certain other rituals such as communion.</p>\n<p>A joined group of priests/adherents functions with the Ritual ML of the leader.</p>\n<p>The leader of the liturgy may also have other options allowed at GM discretion.</p>","source":"HMG PE Religion 10, Glossdex 22","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"diety":"Sávè-k'nôr","circle":4,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"ptPGLX4zqAaa1Zsn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-rituals-agrik.z80UPKcyoy7WrHnd"}}}
{"name":"Haléa's Voice","type":"invocation","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/png/agrik.png","data":{"notes":"","description":"<table style=\"width: 98.8212%; height: 32px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Time to Perform:</strong> Appr. one minute</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Requirement:</strong> Silent prayer or chant/touch improves EML by 10</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Hal&eacute;a&rsquo;s Voice is the voice of persuasion. It may be used to double the invoker&rsquo;s RHETORIC, ORATORY, or INTRIGUE EML for 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>With Critical Success, the cleric can lay a <em>geas</em>. Specific effects are left to GM discretion.</p>\n<p>Optional Rule</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;( ) If used against a single target, reduce EML by the victim&rsquo;s Will.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","source":"HMG PE Religion 10, Glossdex 17","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"diety":"","circle":null,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"ptPGLX4zqAaa1Zsn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-rituals-agrik.z80UPKcyoy7WrHnd"}},"_id":"UY34lBfxV56i2LZt"}
{"_id":"WAlpOwOD9zgfU1Rt","name":"Blessing","type":"invocation","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/png/saveknor.png","data":{"notes":"","description":"<table style=\"width: 98.8212%; height: 32px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Time to Perform:</strong> Appr. 10 seconds</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Requirement:</strong> Prayer/meditation/gesture/touch</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Blessings may not be performed on oneself. The procedure varies &ndash; most churches encourage the laying on of hands, but this is not mandatory. The blessing can take two forms. One is to bestow piety points on the recipient. Another is to grant a (one-time) luck bonus; see <em>Blessing</em> Table below.</p>\n<p>Optional rules:</p>\n<p>&nbsp; ( ) The invoking cleric decides whether to bestow Piety Points or luck.</p>\n<p>&nbsp; ( ) The GM decides whether to bestow PP or luck. This decision may be made by flipping a coin at GM discretion.</p>\n<p>Piety can only be given to adherents of the same religion; it is accrued immediately by the recipient. Luck may be given to anyone and is applied to the <em>next</em> situation calling for luck (GM discretion) &ndash; almost any dice-roll affecting the character's welfare. A blessing may be used to neutralise an \"equivalent\" curse/hex.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width: 491px; height: 64px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 38px; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\"><strong>Piety Gain</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\"><strong>Luck</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 38px; height: 16px;\"><strong>CS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">2d6 pp</td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">15%</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 38px; height: 16px;\"><strong>MS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">1d6 pp</td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">5%</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","source":"HMG PE Religion 10, Glossdex 5","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"diety":"Sávè-k'nôr","circle":3,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"ptPGLX4zqAaa1Zsn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-rituals-agrik.z80UPKcyoy7WrHnd"}}}
{"_id":"ZhmAZbQ1vZoD1T5x","name":"Tongues","type":"invocation","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/png/saveknor.png","data":{"notes":"","description":"<table style=\"width: 98.8212%; height: 32px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Time to Perform:</strong> Appr. 2 minutes</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Requirement:</strong> Prayer/gesture/etc.</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>This Invocation lets the cleric speak and understand any language for 10/30 minutes with MS/CS. CS also allows a Skill Development Roll (SKILLS 4) in the language skill involved.</p>","source":"HMG PE Religion 10, Glossdex 39","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"diety":"Sávè-k'nôr","circle":2,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"ptPGLX4zqAaa1Zsn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-rituals-agrik.z80UPKcyoy7WrHnd"}}}
{"_id":"d7jbtGqs8iGNcv4i","name":"Cure","type":"invocation","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/png/saveknor.png","data":{"notes":"","description":"<table style=\"height: 48px; width: 98.8212%;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Time to Perform:</strong> Appr. one hour</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Requirement:</strong> Prayer/meditation/gesture/touch. The ritual normally uses incense and/or other paraphernalia (if such items are unavailable reduce EML by 10).<strong><br /></strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>An Invocation to help a patient overcome an illness, wound, or disease. Use the Table to determine the effect. The invoker must specify the ailment. Revivification is not possible.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"height: 48px; width: 98.8212%;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 14.6388%; height: 16px;\"><strong>CF/MF</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 84.4106%; height: 16px; text-align: left;\">No effect.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 14.6388%; height: 16px;\"><strong>MS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 84.4106%; height: 16px; text-align: left;\">The success level of all subsequent HEALING ROLLS for the specified ailment is increased by one (eg from MF to MS, or from CF to MF).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 14.6388%; height: 16px;\"><strong>CS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 84.4106%; text-align: left; height: 16px;\">The cure applies to <em>all</em> injuries/diseases (except long term disfigurements, psychological ailments, etc.).</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","source":"HMG PE Religion 10, Glossdex 9","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"diety":"Sávè-k'nôr","circle":2,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"ptPGLX4zqAaa1Zsn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-rituals-agrik.z80UPKcyoy7WrHnd"}}}
{"name":"Battlelust","type":"invocation","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/png/agrik.png","data":{"notes":"","description":"<table style=\"width: 98.8212%; height: 32px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Time to Perform:</strong> Appr. <sup>1</sup>/<sub>2</sub> minute</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Requirement:</strong> Prayer/meditation/gesture</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>An Invocation to whip up frenzy in one&rsquo;s allies in battle. All friendly warriors within range Test Will. If the invoker achieves CF, the invocation works (as MS) on in&ndash;range enemies.</p>\n<p>The altered Morale State lasts for Duration, during which time the affected character(s) make no Initiative or Morale Tests. For explanation of morale states see COMBAT 19.</p>\n<table style=\"width: 491px; height: 80px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 38px; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\"><strong>Duration</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\"><strong>Range</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\"><strong>Will Test</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 38px; height: 16px;\"><strong>CS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">10 minutes</td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">100 yards</td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">5x Will</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 38px; height: 16px;\"><strong>MS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">5 minutes</td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">50 yards</td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">3x Will</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 38px; height: 16px;\"><strong>MF</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 225px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\" colspan=\"3\">No Effect</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 38px; height: 16px;\"><strong>CF</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 225px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\" colspan=\"3\">Effect works (as MS) on all <em>enemies</em> in range.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width: 491px; height: 80px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 16px; width: 338px;\" colspan=\"2\">Each supjects tests Will as indicated:</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 49px; height: 16px;\"><strong>CS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 289px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Subject may <em>choose </em>a morale state.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 49px; height: 16px;\"><strong>MS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 289px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">If subject was BROKEN or CAUTIOUS, s/he becomes NEUTRAL.<br />If subject was NORMAL or DESPERATE, s/he goes BERSERK.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 49px; height: 16px;\"><strong>MF/CS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 289px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">Character becomes DESPERATE</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","source":"HMG PE Religion 10, Glossdex 4","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"diety":"","circle":null,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"ptPGLX4zqAaa1Zsn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-rituals-agrik.z80UPKcyoy7WrHnd"}},"_id":"icYIKUhTfIsUI4Lo"}
{"name":"Endurance","type":"invocation","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/png/agrik.png","data":{"notes":"","description":"<table style=\"width: 98.8212%; height: 32px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Time to Perform:</strong> 10-20 seconds</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Requirement:</strong> Silent prayer/touch</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Temporarily increases the subject&rsquo;s ENDURANCE or CONDITION (as applicable at GM discretion). Use the Endurance Table to determine effect.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width: 491px; height: 97px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10px; height: 16px;\"><strong>Success</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 103px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\"><strong>Effect</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10px; height: 16px;\"><strong>CF/MF</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 103px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">No effect</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 33px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10px; height: 33px;\"><strong>MS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 103px; text-align: center; height: 33px;\">\n<p>Increase END by 2 points for 5 minutes.<br />Or Condition by 10 points for 5 minutes.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10px; height: 16px;\"><strong>CS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 103px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">Increase END 4 points for 15 minutes.<br />Or Condition by 20 points for 15 minutes.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","source":"HMG PE Religion 10, Glossdex 12","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"diety":"","circle":null,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"ptPGLX4zqAaa1Zsn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-rituals-agrik.z80UPKcyoy7WrHnd"}},"_id":"ikKflhvLvqWKwBCB"}
{"_id":"jLV6gmYNaoo56wem","name":"Revivification","type":"invocation","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/png/saveknor.png","data":{"notes":"","description":"<table style=\"width: 98.8212%; height: 32px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Time to Perform:</strong> 12 hours or more</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Requirement:</strong> Prayer/chanting/incense/salves/holy water/etc.</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>An Invocation to bring the dead back to life, although probably not to the prime of health. An invoker can make one attempt per cadaver.</p>\n<p>Once the ceremony is complete, the victim tests the multiple of Endurance given on the Revivification Table.</p>\n<p>Wounds, diseases etc., which may have killed the victim, are only cured sufficiently to permit life, and the patient may still die from them; additional healing is probably advisable.</p>\n<table style=\"width: 98.8743%; height: 64px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 15%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Success</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 85%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\"><strong>Radius</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 15%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\"><strong>CS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 85%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">Victim tests CONDITION</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 15%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\"><strong>MS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 85%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">Victim tests <sup>1</sup>/<sub>2</sub> CONDITION</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 15%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\"><strong>MF/CF</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 85%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">No effect (victim remains dead)</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Optional Rule:</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp; (&nbsp; ) Modify ML for patient&rsquo;s DIVINE ESTRANGEMENT (if rule is in force) and/or the victim&rsquo;s piety. See: Divine Intervention <em>Modifiers</em> (RELIGION 7).</p>","source":"HMG PE Religion 10, Glossdex 30","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"diety":"Sávè-k'nôr","circle":4,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"ptPGLX4zqAaa1Zsn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-rituals-agrik.z80UPKcyoy7WrHnd"}}}
{"name":"Fatigue","type":"invocation","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/png/agrik.png","data":{"notes":"","description":"<table style=\"width: 98.8212%; height: 32px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Time to Perform:</strong> Appr. one minute</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Requirement:</strong> Silent prayer or chant/touch improves EML by 10</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>An Invocation designed to drain a victim&rsquo;s energy. Any single person in plain view and within 20 yards may be targeted. See Fatigue Table.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width: 491px; height: 97px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10px; height: 16px;\"><strong>Success</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 103px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\"><strong>Effect</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10px; height: 16px;\"><strong>CF</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 103px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Invoker accrues 4d6 FATIGUE POINTS.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10px; height: 16px;\"><strong>MF</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 103px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">No effect</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 33px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10px; height: 33px;\"><strong>MS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 103px; text-align: center; height: 33px;\">\n<p>Victim accrues 3d6 fatigue points.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10px; height: 16px;\"><strong>CS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 103px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">Victim accrues 5d6 fatigue points.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Fatigue accrued by means of this ritual is indistinguishable from fatigue acquired by other methods</p>","source":"HMG PE Religion 10, Glossdex 14","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"diety":"","circle":null,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"ptPGLX4zqAaa1Zsn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-rituals-agrik.z80UPKcyoy7WrHnd"}},"_id":"kwtcqumNaAcRQQua"}
{"name":"Awe","type":"invocation","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/png/agrik.png","data":{"notes":"","description":"<table style=\"width: 98.8212%; height: 32px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Time to Perform:</strong> Appr. 1 minute</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Requirement:</strong> Prayer/meditation</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>This invocation creates a feeling of the presence of the deity and is used during ceremonies in some churches. Proselytising clerics sometimes use the Awe Invocation to make converts, and priests may use it to restore the faith of a &ldquo;lost sheep&rdquo;. The duration and range of the effect are given on the Awe Effect Table.</p>\n<p>In combat or other crises, the invocation&rsquo;s effect is to cause godless persons or adherents of opposing deities to test INITIATIVE (COMBAT 19). If the Initiative Testing rule is not in use, it may be used just for this purpose. Alternately (at GM discretion) a Will test may be used in its place. If the invoker achieves CS, the victim&rsquo;s Initiative EML is reduced by 10. If Will is to be tested, the multiple is given under &ldquo;will test&rdquo;.</p>\n<table style=\"width: 491px; height: 80px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 38px; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\"><strong>Duration</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\"><strong>Range</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\"><strong>Initiative</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\"><strong>Will Test</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 38px; height: 16px;\"><strong>CS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">10 minutes</td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">50 yards</td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">-10</td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">(3x Will)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 38px; height: 16px;\"><strong>MS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">5 minutes</td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">100 yards</td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">&ndash;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">(5x Will)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 38px; height: 16px;\"><strong>MF</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 384px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\" colspan=\"4\">No Effect</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 38px; height: 16px;\"><strong>CF</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 384px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\" colspan=\"4\">Effect is felt by the invoker (Initiative -5, Test = 4x Will)</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Optional Rule:<br /><strong>CS: </strong>The effect may be directed at specific individual(s) rather than as a blanket effect.</p>","source":"HMG PE Religion 10, Glossdex 4","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"diety":"","circle":null,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"ptPGLX4zqAaa1Zsn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-rituals-agrik.z80UPKcyoy7WrHnd"}},"_id":"qMCZDrloYNazK3IM"}
{"name":"Courage","type":"invocation","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/png/agrik.png","data":{"notes":"","description":"<table style=\"height: 48px; width: 98.8212%;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Time to Perform:</strong> Appr. 10-60 seconds</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Requirement:</strong>&nbsp;Prayer &amp;&nbsp;gesture<strong><br /></strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Range:&nbsp;</strong>20 yards<strong><br /></strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Temporarily increases the Will attribute of an individual (usually a friend).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"height: 64px; width: 98.8212%;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 38px; height: 16px;\"><strong>CS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: left;\">Will raised five points for half an hour.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 38px; height: 16px;\"><strong>MS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; height: 16px; text-align: left;\">Will raised by two points for ten minutes.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 38px; height: 16px;\"><strong>MF</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; text-align: left; height: 16px;\">No effect</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 38px; height: 16px;\"><strong>CF</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 75px; text-align: left; height: 16px;\">Will halved for ten minutes.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>If the INITIATIVE TESTING rules are in use, the target individual is immune to Initiative Testing for the Duration.</p>","source":"HMG PE Religion 10, Glossdex 9","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"diety":"","circle":null,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"ptPGLX4zqAaa1Zsn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-rituals-agrik.z80UPKcyoy7WrHnd"}},"_id":"rkYgAL2HognUcAZ2"}
{"_id":"vXQFC9vi1ehvu36s","name":"Consecration","type":"invocation","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/png/saveknor.png","data":{"notes":"","description":"<table style=\"width: 98.8212%; height: 32px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Time to Perform:</strong> 10-120 minutes</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Requirement:</strong> Prayer/meditation/holy water etc.</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>A ceremony to bless an object or place so that it becomes a holy artefact or place. The effect is highly variable. Temples and graveyards are usually consecrated ground, and saintly relics may also be religious</p>\n<p>artefacts. Consecration is never undertaken lightly; a wise cleric does not consecrate something inappropriate. Water that is consecrated becomes holy water &ndash; this is simply a method of &ldquo;storing a blessing&rdquo;. The same principle can apply to symbolic items in various churches: &Agrave;gr&iacute;kans use consecrated fire/smoke; Hal&eacute;ans consecrate incense, aphrodisiacs, etc.; priests of S&aacute;v&egrave;-k'n&ocirc;r often employ consecrated books and scrolls.</p>","source":"HMG PE Religion 10, Glossdex 8","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"diety":"Sávè-k'nôr","circle":3,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"ptPGLX4zqAaa1Zsn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-rituals-agrik.z80UPKcyoy7WrHnd"}}}
{"name":"Darkness","type":"invocation","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/png/agrik.png","data":{"notes":"","description":"<table style=\"width: 98.8212%; height: 32px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Time to Perform:</strong> Appr. one minute</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 98.6083%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Requirement:</strong> Prayer/meditation/gesture/touch/verbal declaration</td>\n<td style=\"width: 0.397614%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>An invocation to make the immediate environment darker. The invoker can see normally if the invocation is successful. See Darkness Table for result(s).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width: 491px; height: 97px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 113px; text-align: center;\" colspan=\"2\"><strong>Reduce EML by 25 if attempted in full daylight</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10px; height: 16px;\"><strong>Success</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 103px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\"><strong>Effect</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10px; height: 16px;\"><strong>CF</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 103px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">\n<p>The invoker is blinded for 2d6 minutes.</p>\n<p>Optional rule:<br />( ) In some cases, the invoker is blinded until an appropriate penance has been performed&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10px; height: 16px;\"><strong>MF</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 103px; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">No effect</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 33px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10px; height: 33px;\"><strong>MS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 103px; text-align: center; height: 33px;\">Illumination reduced by half for five minutes over a radius of 20 yards from the invoker.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 10px; height: 16px;\"><strong>CS</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 103px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">Total darkness prevails for up to ten minutes (same range).</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","source":"HMG PE Religion 10, Glossdex 10","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"diety":"","circle":null,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"ptPGLX4zqAaa1Zsn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-rituals-agrik.z80UPKcyoy7WrHnd"}},"_id":"xUrr7JzPdvkO2Dtj"}
